description: a(1)=a(2)=1, then a(n+1)=floor(a(n)/3) if this is not among 0,a(1),...,a(n), else a(n+1)=a(n)+a(n-1).
comments: Numbers appearing among the terms more than once include 1, 50, 265, 341, 516, 570, 622, ... - _Ivan Neretin_, Sep 04 2015
links: Ivan Neretin, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: a = {0, 1, 1}; Do[AppendTo[a, If[MemberQ[a, c = Quotient[a[[-1]], 3]], a[[-1]] + a[[-2]], c]], {n, 3, 59}]; Delete[a, 1] (* _Ivan Neretin_, Sep 04 2015 *)
